**Tender Details:**
A request for a standing offer is being issued for the purchase and delivery of eleven (11) floating dock sections. The deadline for submission of proposals is **December 20, 2023, at 14:00 hours.**

The selected bidder(s) will be required to deliver the floating dock sections to the designated location in Montreal.

**Key Purchase Details:**

* Eleven (11) floating dock sections
* Brief technical specifications:
	+ *Temporary construction and maintenance support equipment and materials*
	+ Corresponding to UNSPSC code: *30191800*
* Suppliers are required to have a valid World Trade Organization Agreement on Government Procurement (WTO GPA) certification.

**Trade Agreements:**
This tender is covered by the following trade agreements:
* World Trade Organization Agreement on Government Procurement (WTO GPA)
* Canada-UK Trade Continuity Agreement (Canada-UK TCA)
* North American Free Trade Agreement (NAFTA)
* [and other related trade agreements]

**Methods of Tendering:**
The purchasing method is competitive and open to all eligible bidders.

**Evaluation Criteria:**
Bidders will be evaluated based on **Lowest Price**.

**Submission Guidelines:**
Bidders must submit their proposals electronically via the designated portal. Detailed submission guidelines and instructions are available on the notice URL.
